sec.p:
Therefore, when the remaining 12 items were put into EFA, Bartlett’s test of sphericity was showed as statistically significant (χ2=942.303, df= 66, p <0.001), and the Kaiser–Meyer–Olkin measure (KMO) was 0.841, which was adequate for factor analysis (Table 3). Factors with an eigenvalue of 1 or more were extracted and considered a marked decline in the slopes of the scree plot when we run with JASP software (version 0.16.1).Table 3
